ZH: 我需要忏悔我偷了你的钱包。
EN: I need to repent for stealing your wallet.

ZH: 他因为言辞尖刻而感到忏悔。
EN: He feels remorseful for his sharp words.

ZH: 她向神忏悔她做的坏事。
EN: She repents to God for the wrong she has done.

ZH: 忏悔是改变错误行为的第一步。
EN: Repentance is the first step to changing wrong behavior.

ZH: 我忏悔没有好好利用我的时间。
EN: I repent for not making good use of my time.

ZH: 忏悔可以带来内心的平静。
EN: Repentance can bring inner peace.

ZH: 这是她的忏悔信。
EN: This is her letter of repentance.

ZH: 我真诚地忏悔我的过错。
EN: I sincerely repent for my mistakes.

ZH: 他坚信忏悔可以赦免罪行。
EN: He firmly believes that repentance can forgive sins.

ZH: 她的忏悔感动了他的心。
EN: Her repentance touched his heart.

ZH: 忏悔并不意味着一切都会得到原谅。
EN: Repentance does not necessarily mean forgiveness.

ZH: 我深感忏悔，对不起。
EN: I deeply repent and apologize.

ZH: 忏悔是一种解脱心灵的方式。
EN: Repentance is a way to free the soul.

ZH: 他每天都在忏悔自己的过错。
EN: He repents for his mistakes every day.

ZH: 忏悔让我意识到了我的错误。
EN: Repentance made me realize my mistakes.

ZH: 她已经下定决心要忏悔。
EN: She has made up her mind to repent.

ZH: 我忏悔辜负了你的期望。
EN: I repent for disappointing your expectations.

ZH: 忏悔是一种内心的净化。
EN: Repentance is a purification of the heart.

ZH: 我会忏悔我所做的不对之处。
EN: I will repent for what I have done wrong.

ZH: 他对过去的行为感到忏悔不已。
EN: He feels deep remorse for his past actions.
